## /api/athlete/{firstname_lastname}
### Retrieve an Athlete [GET]
Returns the details of an athlete.
+ Parameters

    + firstname_lastname (required, string, `meghan_aghosta`) ... first name and last name of the Athlete to perform action with, separated with "_".

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Body

                {
                    "id": 6,
                    "first_name": "Meghan",
                    "last_name": "Agosta",
                    "country": 7,
                    "gender": "Female",
                    "birthdate": "1987-02-12",
                    "height": "1.68 m (5' 6'')",
                    "weight": "67 kg / 148 lbs",
                    "gold_medals": [11],
                    "silver_medals": [],
                    "bronze_medals": []
                }
                
+ Response 404 (application/json)

    + Body
    
            {
                "message":"error",
                "errors":["not found"]
            }

# Group Countries
Countries related resources. A country has the following attributes:

* Id
* Name
* Description
* Total of Gold Medals
* Total of Silver Medals
* Total of Bronze Medals
* List of Athletes

## /api/country
### List of all Countries [GET]
Returns a list of countries and their ids.
